      "assignees": [],
      "body": "## Problem\n\nThe current JavaScript demo relies on CommonJS module patterns, which limits compatibility with modern JavaScript tooling and makes module bundling workflows harder to configure. This is related to the JavaScript demo issues tracked in #26.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nMigrate the JavaScript demo to use ESM imports and a modern module system, including package metadata and build tooling that supports modern JavaScript workflows.\n\n## Benefits\n\n- Improves compatibility with modern JavaScript development practices.\n- Makes ESM imports the default style for demo code.\n- Simplifies module bundling expectations for downstream users.\n- Aligns the demo with modern JavaScript ecosystem conventions.\n- Provides a clearer path away from CommonJS limitations.",
      "labels": [
        "enhancement"
      ],
      "milestone": 0,
      "owner": "mangowhoiscloud",
      "repo": "harmony",
      "title": "Upgrade JavaScript demo to use ESM imports with modern module system",
      "type": "enhancement"
    },
