  {
    "tool": "add_issue_comment",
    "input": {
      "body": "Findings from the implementation attempt in PR #28:\n\nThe attempted ESM migration uncovered **technical constraints** that prevent the JavaScript demo from safely moving to ESM at this time. The current demo path still has a **CommonJS dependency** in how it integrates with harmony internals, and those **harmony core limitations** affect initialization, exports, and tokenization behavior.\n\nDetailed explanation:\n\n- Setting the demo package to `type: \"module\"` changes how Node and bundlers interpret the package entry points.\n- The current harmony integration expects CommonJS-compatible loading patterns, which makes a direct ESM import path unsafe.\n- The webpack entry configuration introduces **build system compatibility** concerns because it must bridge ESM source syntax with CommonJS-oriented runtime assumptions.\n- Resolving this properly would require deeper changes to the core package/module boundary rather than a demo-only update.\n\nFor these reasons, the ESM migration is **not viable at this time** and should not proceed until the underlying module architecture can support it.",
      "issue_number": 27,
      "owner": "mangowhoiscloud",
      "repo": "harmony"
    },
    "result": {
      "result": "{\"meta\": null, \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\\"id\\\":4881558644,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOTNWqZ88AAAABIvasdA\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Findings from the implementation attempt in PR #28:\\\\n\\\\nThe attempted ESM migration uncovered **technical constraints** that prevent the JavaScript demo from safely moving to ESM at this time. The current demo path still has a **CommonJS dependency** in how it integrates with harmony internals, and those **harmony core limitations** affect initialization, exports, and tokenization behavior.\\\\n\\\\nDetailed explanation:\\\\n\\\\n- Setting the demo package to `type: \\\\\\\"module\\\\\\\"` changes how Node and bundlers interpret the package entry points.\\\\n- The current harmony integration expects CommonJS-compatible loading patterns, which makes a direct ESM import path unsafe.\\\\n- The webpack entry configuration introduces **build system compatibility** concerns because it must bridge ESM source syntax with CommonJS-oriented runtime assumptions.\\\\n- Resolving this properly would require deeper changes to the core package/module boundary rather than a demo-only update.\\\\n\\\\nFor these reasons, the ESM migration is **not viable at this time** and should not proceed until the underlying module architecture can support it.\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?u=1219d9f19299efb22d775f3f70b4fb0e02679925\\\\u0026v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.