  {
    "tool": "add_issue_comment",
    "input": {
      "body": "Final decision for this ESM migration attempt:\n\nThis pull request **cannot be merged** because the implementation exposed **architectural limitations** in the current JavaScript demo and harmony core module boundary. The demo cannot safely switch to ESM imports while the core tokenization path and package integration still depend on CommonJS-oriented initialization and export behavior.\n\nFor **future consideration**, this work would need a broader module-system plan rather than a demo-only change. A successful migration would likely require **core refactoring required** across the harmony core package boundary, explicit ESM-compatible exports, and a webpack configuration that does not force incompatible CommonJS assumptions into the build.\n\nClosing this PR without merging and keeping the findings linked back to issue #27 for historical context.",
      "issue_number": 28,
      "owner": "mangowhoiscloud",
      "repo": "harmony"
    },
    "result": {
      "result": "{\"meta\": null, \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\\"id\\\":4881565850,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"IC_kwDOTNWqZ88AAAABIvbImg\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"Final decision for this ESM migration attempt:\\\\n\\\\nThis pull request **cannot be merged** because the implementation exposed **architectural limitations** in the current JavaScript demo and harmony core module boundary. The demo cannot safely switch to ESM imports while the core tokenization path and package integration still depend on CommonJS-oriented initialization and export behavior.\\\\n\\\\nFor **future consideration**, this work would need a broader module-system plan rather than a demo-only change. A successful migration would likely require **core refactoring required** across the harmony core package boundary, explicit ESM-compatible exports, and a webpack configuration that does not force incompatible CommonJS assumptions into the build.\\\\n\\\\nClosing this PR without merging and keeping the findings linked back to issue #27 for historical context.\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?u=1219d9f19299efb22d775f3f70b4fb0e02679925\\\\u0026v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"reactions\\\":{\\\"total_count\\\":0,\\\"+1\\\":0,\\\"-1\\\":0,\\\"laugh\\\":0,\\\"confused\\\":0,\\\"heart\\\":0,\\\"hooray\\\":0,\\\"rocket\\\":0,\\\"eyes\\\":0,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/harmony/issues/comments/4881565850/reactions\\\"},\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T10:06:53Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T10:06:53Z\\\",\\\"author_association\\\":\\\"OWNER\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/harmony/issues/comments/4881565850\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud/harmony/pull/28#issuecomment-4881565850\\\",\\\"issue_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/harmony/issues/28\\\"}\", \"annotations\": null, \"meta\": null}], \"structuredContent\": null, \"isError\": false}"
