    "tool": "update_issue",
    "input": {
      "assignees": [],
      "body": "## Summary\n\nThis pull request attempts an ESM migration for the JavaScript demo so it can use ESM imports and align with modern JavaScript module practices. It explores whether the demo can move away from CommonJS while preserving the existing harmony integration.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Adds `type: \"module\"` to the JavaScript demo package metadata.\n- Adds a webpack configuration entry through the demo build script.\n- Introduces an ESM-style `src/main.js` entry point using `import { HarmonyEncoding } from '@openai/harmony'`.\n- Documents the migration attempt and the expected module compatibility risks.\n\n## Issues Discovered\n\nDuring the ESM migration attempt, technical problems were identified around module compatibility and breaking changes. The harmony core integration still depends on CommonJS-oriented loading behavior, and the webpack configuration does not resolve those constraints cleanly for this demo.\n\nAddresses #27\n\nKeywords: ESM migration, webpack configuration, module compatibility, breaking changes",
      "duplicate_of": 0,
      "issue_number": 28,
      "labels": [
        "enhancement",
        "needs-investigation",
        "wontfix"
